To make the timeline more interactive, we can add a hover effect on the events.  Let's add a background color to the event element when the user hovers over it. 

```css
/* styles.css */
/*... existing styles... */

.event {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    padding: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.event::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 2px;
    background-color: #007bff;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
}

.event:hover {
    background-color: #f9f9f9;
}

.event:hover::after {
    background-color: #007bff;
